snippet.textDisplay: After watching Ladbaby’s vlogs for a while  I have seen how much they’ve accomplished, from having their two beautiful children and both parents getting celebrity mum/dad of the year, it’s all been a pleasure to watch, However, I’ve seen both vlogs of them going to the Brits seeing how much effort they go to and seeing the joy on there face, the first time they was sat right at the back and this year slightly closer. They aren’t musicians as such, and the two singles they have realised aren’t to everyone’s touch. However they have had two Christmas number ones and all the money made from both singles went to charity. And watching Mark feeling disappointed in his recent vlog is painful to watch. They had worked hard towards getting those two Christmas number ones and they get nothing from it? Whether it’s jealously or down to the fact people view you tubers as nothing I’ll never know however if you spent the time of day watching a vlog of them you’d fall in love with the pure love and passion Mark shares for his family and vlogging! All in favours of starting a petition to get Mark and Roxanne invited to the brits to sit in the celebrity section say “I”
